  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 1170 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-chicken-potato-stew-655b9b1fd1348f59373b1e94
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces.

== Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Stew ==

Open package of chicken and drain off any excess liquid. Heat @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} in a single layer. Season with @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Add garlic and scallion whites; cook, stirring constantly, until chicken is cooked through and aromatics are fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Increase heat to high. Stir in potatoes, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and @water{2 1/2%cups}; cover and bring to a boil. Uncover, reduce heat to medium, and simmer, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Whisk @mirepoix paste{1%ounce}, @cheese roux concentrate{1%ounce}, and @cream cheese{2%tablespoon} into pot with stew until combined and slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a fork.

Divide stew and rice between shallow #bowls{} in separate sections. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.